<inglise> Council Regulation (EC) No 2424/2001 of 6 December 2001 on the development of the second generation Schengen Information System (SIS II) </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2424/2001 teise p&otilde;lvkonna Schengeni infos&uuml;steemi (SIS II) v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamise kohta 6. detsember 2001 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 66 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 66, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the initiative of the Kingdom of Belgium and the Kingdom of Sweden(1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Belgia Kuningriigi ja Rootsi Kuningriigi algatust, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament(2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) The Schengen Information System, set up pursuant to the provisions of Title IV of the Convention of 1990 implementing the Schengen Agreement of 14 June 1985 on the gradual abolition of checks at common borders, hereinafter referred to as "the 1990 Schengen Convention", constitutes an essential tool for the application of the provisions of the Schengen acquis as integrated into the framework of the European Union. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) kontrolli j&auml;rkj&auml;rgulist kaotamist &uuml;hispiiridel k&auml;sitleva 14. juuni 1985. aasta Schengeni lepingu rakendamise 1990. aasta konventsiooni, edaspidi "1990. aasta Schengeni konventsioon", IV jaotise kohaselt loodud Schengeni infos&uuml;steem on t&auml;htis vahend Euroopa Liitu integreeritud Schengeni acquis' kohaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) The Schengen Information System in its current form has the capacity to service no more than 18 participating States. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) Schengeni infos&uuml;steem oma praegusel kujul suudab teenindada k&otilde;ige rohkem 18 osalisriiki. </eesti>
<inglise> It is at present operational for 13 Member States and 2 other States (Iceland and Norway) and is intended to become operational for the United Kingdom and Ireland in the foreseeable future. </inglise>
<eesti> Praegu kasutatakse seda 13 liikmesriigis ja 2 muus riigis (Island ja Norra) ning l&auml;hitulevikus kavatsetakse seda hakata kasutama &Uuml;hendkuningriigis ja Iirimaal. </eesti>
<inglise> It has, however, not been constructed so as to service the increased number of Member States of the European Union after its enlargement. </inglise>
<eesti> See ei ole aga rajatud nii, et see suudaks teenindada Euroopa Liidu laienemise j&auml;rel suurenevat liikmesriikide hulka; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) For this reason, and in order to benefit from the latest developments in the field of information technology and to allow for the introduction of new functions, it is necessary to develop a new, second generation Schengen Information System (SIS II), as already acknowledged in Decision SCH/Com-ex (97) 24 of the Executive Committee of 7 October 1997(3). </inglise>
<eesti> 3) nii seet&otilde;ttu kui ka infotehnoloogia vallas tehtud viimastest edusammudest kasusaamiseks ja uute toimingute sisseseadmise v&otilde;imaldamiseks on vaja v&auml;lja t&ouml;&ouml;tada uus, teise p&otilde;lvkonna Schengeni infos&uuml;steem (SIS II), nagu on juba m&auml;rgitud t&auml;itevkomitee 7. oktoobri 1997. aasta otsuses SCH/Com-ex (97) 24; (3) </eesti>
<inglise> (4) The expenditure involved in the development of SIS II is to be charged to the budget of the European Union in accordance with the Council conclusions to that effect of 29 May 2001. </inglise>
<eesti> 4) SIS II v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamisega seotud kulud kaetakse Euroopa Liidu eelarvest koosk&otilde;las n&otilde;ukogu 19. mai 2001. aasta sellekohaste j&auml;reldustega. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation constitutes, together with Council Decision 2001/886/JHA of 6 December 2001 on the development of the second generation Schengen Information System (SIS II) (4), the required legislative basis to allow for the inclusion in the budget of the Union of the necessary appropriations for the development of SIS II and the execution of that part of the budget. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus moodustab &uuml;heskoos teise p&otilde;lvkonna Schengeni infos&uuml;steemi (SIS II) v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamist k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 6. detsembri 2001. aasta otsusega 2001/886/JSK (4) vajaliku &otilde;igusliku aluse liidu eelarves SIS II v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamiseks vajalike assigneeringute tegemisele ja k&otilde;nealuse eelarveosa t&auml;itmisele; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) The legislative basis consists of two parts: this Regulation based on Article 66 of the Treaty establishing the European Community and a Council Decision based on Article 30(1) (a) and (b), Article 31(a) and (b) and Article 34(2) (c) of the Treaty on European Union. </inglise>
<eesti> 5) &otilde;iguslik alus koosneb kahest osast: k&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus, mis p&otilde;hineb Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingu artiklil 66, ja n&otilde;ukogu otsus, mis p&otilde;hineb Euroopa Liidu lepingu artikli 30 l&otilde;ike 1 punktidel a ja b, artikli 31 punktidel a ja b ja artikli 34 l&otilde;ike 2 punktil c. </eesti>
<inglise> The reason for this is that, as set out in Article 92 of the 1990 Schengen Convention, the Schengen Information System is to enable the authorities designated by the Member States, by means of an automated search procedure, to have access to alerts on persons and property for the purposes of border checks and other police and customs checks carried out within the country in accordance with national law, as well as for the purposes of issuing visas, residence permits and the administration of legislation on aliens in the context of the application of the provisions of the Schengen acquis relating to the movement of persons. </inglise>
<eesti> Selle p&otilde;hjuseks on asjaolu, et 1990. aasta Schengeni konventsiooni artikli 92 kohaselt saavad Schengeni infos&uuml;steemi kaudu liikmesriikide m&auml;&auml;ratud asutused automatiseeritud otsingumenetluse abil k&auml;tte m&auml;rked isikute ja esemete kohta, et teha piirikontrolle ja muid siseriiklike &otilde;iguse kohaselt riigis tehtavaid politsei- ja tollikontrolle ning v&auml;ljastada viisasid ja elamislube ja kohaldada v&auml;lismaalasi k&auml;sitlevaid &otilde;igusnorme seoses isikute liikumist k&auml;sitleva Schengeni aquis' kohaldamisega; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) The fact that the legislative basis required for allowing the development of SIS II to be financed by the Union budget consists of two separate instruments does not affect the principle that the Schengen Information System constitutes, and should continue to constitute, one single, integrated, information system and that SIS II must be developed as such. </inglise>
<eesti> 6) asjaolu, et SIS II v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamise rahastamiseks liidu eelarvest vajalik &otilde;iguslik alus koosneb kahest eri &otilde;igusaktist, ei m&otilde;juta p&otilde;him&otilde;tet, et Schengeni infos&uuml;steem moodustab ja peaks ka edaspidi moodustama &uuml;he, &uuml;htse ja tervikliku infos&uuml;steemi ja et SIS II tuleb v&auml;lja t&ouml;&ouml;tada selle p&otilde;him&otilde;tte kohaselt; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) This Regulation is without prejudice to the adoption in future of the necessary legislation describing in detail the operation and use of SIS II, such as, but not limited to, rules defining the categories of data to be entered into the system, the purposes for which they are to be entered and the criteria for their entry, rules concerning the content of SIS records, including responsibility for their correctness, rules on the duration of alerts, interlinking of alerts and compatibility between alerts, rules on access to SIS data and rules on the protection of personal data and their control. </inglise>
<eesti> 7) k&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus ei piira tulevikus selliste vajalike &otilde;igusnormide vastuv&otilde;tmist, milles kirjeldatakse &uuml;ksikasjalikult SIS II toimimist ja kasutamist, nagu muu hulgas s&auml;tted, millega m&auml;&auml;ratletakse s&uuml;steemi sisestatavate andmete liigitus, nende sisestamise eesm&auml;rk ja alused, s&auml;tted, mis k&auml;sitlevad SIS kirjete sisu, sealhulgas vastutust nende &otilde;igsuse eest, s&auml;tted m&auml;rgete kehtivusaja, m&auml;rgete omavahelise sidumise ja &uuml;htesobivuse kohta, s&auml;tted SISis sisalduvatele andmetele juurdep&auml;&auml;su kohta ning s&auml;tted isikuandmete kaitse ja nende kontrolli kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) The measures necessary for the implementation of this Regulation should be adopted in accordance with Council Decision 1999/468/EC of 28 June 1999 laying down the procedures for the exercise of implementing powers conferred on the Commission(5). </inglise>
<eesti> 8) k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse rakendamiseks vajalikud meetmed tuleks vastu v&otilde;tta koosk&otilde;las n&otilde;ukogu 28. juuni 1999. aasta otsusega 1999/468/E&Uuml;, (5) millega kehtestatakse komisjoni rakendusvolituste kasutamise menetlused; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) This Regulation constitutes a development of provisions of the Schengen acquis which fall within the area referred to in Article 1, point G of Council Decision 1999/437/EC of 17 May 1999 on certain arrangements for the application of the Agreement concluded by the Council of the European Union and the Republic of Iceland and the Kingdom of Norway concerning the association of those two States with the implementation, application and development of the Schengen acquis(6) and Article 8(2) of Council Decision 2000/365/EC of 29 May 2000 concerning the request of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland to take part in some of the provisions of the Schengen acquis(7). </inglise>
<eesti> 9) k&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus kujutab endast nende Schengeni aquis' s&auml;tete edasiarendamist, mis on seotud n&otilde;ukogu 17. mai 1999. aasta otsuse 1999/437/E&Uuml; (Euroopa Liidu N&otilde;ukogu ning Islandi Vabariigi ja Norra Kuningriigi vahel nimetatud kahe riigi Schengeni aquis' s&auml;tete rakendamises, kohaldamises ja edasiarendamises osalemise kohta s&otilde;lmitud lepingu teatavate rakenduseeskirjade kohta) (6) artikli 1 punktis g osutatud valdkonna ja n&otilde;ukogu 29. mai 2000. aasta otsuse 2000/365/E&Uuml; (Suurbritannia ja P&otilde;hja-Iiri &Uuml;hendkuningriigi taotluse kohta osaleda teatavates Schengeni aquis' s&auml;tetes) (7) artikli 8 l&otilde;ikega 2; </eesti>
<inglise> (10) An arrangement has to be made to allow representatives of Iceland and Norway to be associated with the work of committees assisting the Commission in the exercise of its implementing powers. </inglise>
<eesti> 10) tuleb ette n&auml;ha kord, mille alusel Islandi ja Norra esindajad saaksid osaleda komisjoni tema rakendusvolituste kasutamisel abistavate komiteede t&ouml;&ouml;s. </eesti>
<inglise> Such an arrangement has been contemplated in the Exchange of Letters between the Community and Iceland and Norway, annexed to the abovementioned Association Agreement(8). </inglise>
<eesti> Sellist korda on kavandatud &uuml;henduse ning Islandi ja Norra kirjavahetuses, mis on lisatud eespool nimetatud osalemist k&auml;sitlevale kokkuleppele; (8) </eesti>
<inglise> (11) In accordance with Article 3 of the Protocol on the position of the United Kingdom and Ireland annexed to the Treaty on European Union and the Treaty establishing the European Community, the United Kingdom gave notice, by letter of 6 September 2001, of its wish to take part in the adoption and application of this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> 11) Euroopa Liidu lepingule ja Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingule lisatud &Uuml;hendkuningriigi ja Iirimaa seisukohta k&auml;sitleva protokolli artikli 3 kohaselt teatas &Uuml;hendkuningriik 6. septembri 2001. aasta kirjaga oma soovist osaleda k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse vastuv&otilde;tmises ja kohaldamises; </eesti>
<inglise> (12) This Regulation and the United Kingdom's participation in its adoption and application are without prejudice to the arrangements for the United Kingdom's partial participation in the Schengen acquis defined by the Council in Decision 2000/365/EC. </inglise>
<eesti> 12) k&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus ja &Uuml;hendkuningriigi osalemine selle vastuv&otilde;tmisel ja kohaldamisel ei piira n&otilde;ukogu otsuses 2000/365/E&Uuml; kinnitatud korra kohaldamist, mis k&auml;sitleb &Uuml;hendkuningriigi osalist osalemist Schengeni aquis's; </eesti>
<inglise> (13) In accordance with Articles 1 and 2 of the Protocol on the position of Denmark, annexed to the Treaty on European Union and the Treaty establishing the European Community, Denmark is not taking part in the adoption of this Regulation and is therefore not bound by it or subject to its application. </inglise>
<eesti> 13) Euroopa Liidu lepingule ja Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingule lisatud Taani seisukohta k&auml;sitleva protokolli artiklite 1 ja 2 kohaselt ei osale Taani k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse vastuv&otilde;tmisel, mist&otilde;ttu see ei ole talle siduv ega kuulu tema suhtes kohaldamisele. </eesti>
<inglise> Given the fact that this Regulation builds upon the Schengen acquis under the provisions of Title IV of Part Three of the Treaty establishing the European Community, Denmark shall, in accordance with Article 5 of the said Protocol decide within a period of six months after the adoption of this instrument whether it will implement it in its national law, </inglise>
<eesti> Arvestades asjaolu, et k&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus arendab Schengeni aquic'd edasi Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingu kolmanda osa IV jaotise alusel, otsustab Taani k&otilde;nealuse protokolli artikli 5 kohaselt kuue kuu jooksul k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse vastuv&otilde;tmisest, kas ta rakendab seda oma siseriiklikus &otilde;iguses, </eesti>
